originalText.text: ! Dr Rosenthal ruined my vision and quality of life. He never informed me that I would need reading glasses for everything close. He only asked if I read a lot!!! I am now left with vestibular dysfunction because I lost my nearsighted vision and I get dizzy and feel off balance!! Dr Rosenthal has absolutely NO Compassion!! He is in it for the money!!!His assistants even told me that he never explains and informs his patients of the risks to surgery!!! The fact of the matter is that I didn’t even need cataract surgery. I was told by my original Opthomalogist who moved far away. That’s the tragedy for me!!!! If I could give zero stars I would!!!  Stay away from this dr!!!!

originalText.text: Working for Dr Rosenthal is a privilege. I believe he listens to his patients concerns and accommodates their needs by personalizing his surgeries per patient. Understandably, with greatness comes patience. Sometimes a wait can be longer than expected however; knowing we will obtain great care is why we choose our doctors, no? Allow him your time and he will make it worth it.
